Blaze climbed out of the CR chamber, the chamber reported that all traces of
the virus were dormant, as long as there wasn&#39;t a catylist to reactivate it
she&#39;d be fine. She moved closer to the chamber containing Silver Scout and
activated the reactivation program. The chamber opened and the sleek female
of Silver scouts bot form stepped out.

&quot;What did you do to me?&quot; the mutant asked, confused at how her bot form was
returned to her. &quot;I thought I&#39;d lost this form forever.&quot;

Blaze took her weapon from her side, ready in case the mutant had any ideas
about fighting her. &quot;We used the chamber to make your mutation dormant.&quot;
There were to many questions to ask to guess at and there was only one bot
who had the answers she was looking for. &quot;Now it&#39;s your turn to answer a few
questions like who you are and what you&#39;re doing here?&quot;

Silver scout thought for a moment but decided that she didn&#39;t owe Veratis
anything for anything he did to her. &quot;My names Silver Scout, I was near the
Alliance base looking for someone when I caught a familiar scent.&quot; She
wasn&#39;t sure exactly how to explain her mutation. She still wanted to keep
Veratis&#39; secret in case she needed something to fall back on. &quot;When I was
created the sequencers used DNA from another bot. She was the one I followed
here.&quot;

Blaze sensed a half truth in there somewhere but decided that it would be
more important to focus on the mutation virus and how to permanently stop
it. She&#39;d seen how Silver Scout had lost her robot mode, there was no way in
the pit that Blaze wanted to go through the same thing.
